Description:
For entertainers and big families
Located in a quiet cul-de-sac directly overlooking the vast greenery of the Eastern Golf Club, this impressive residence features a tri-level floorplan featuring 5 large bedrooms with built-in and walk-in robes, 4 bathrooms and a powder room. Perfect for blended, extended or multigenerational families, there are multiple living areas, 2 kitchens and a butler’s pantry and 2 indoor/outdoor areas, including a self-contained two-bedroom unit on the lower ground floor. Generous dimensions are further enhanced by high ceilings with wide cornices and gleaming floors with high skirtings. The ground floor features a formal lounge at the front, while the rear of the house opens up to a spectacular entertaining zone comprising family room, meals area, dining alcove, kitchen and a semi-enclosed sunroom with a wet bar, bi-fold windows and views towards the city. The main kitchen is a stunner, boasting waterfall stone bench tops, glass splashbacks, stainless steel AEG appliances and soft-close drawers. The adjoining butler’s pantry has a sink, a rangehood and Smeg gas cooktop, accompanied by a pantry and storeroom. The lower ground level comprises a living/dining/kitchen zone and 2 large ensuite bedrooms. With independent entry, this apartment flows out to a covered alfresco entertaining area. On the top floor, 3 robed bedrooms enjoy 2 bathrooms, a quiet retreat and a large rumpus room with balcony access. The automated double garage has internal access and there’s also video intercom, ducted vacuum, gas boosted solar hot water, solar electricity and a water tank. Excellent nearby amenities include: a local gym and international supermarket, buses, Park+Ride and freeway access, Westfield Doncaster and restaurants.
Insights: 5 Iskandar Place, Doncaster VIC 3108 was last sold in 2017 and 29 other 5 bedroom house in Doncaster have recently been sold.

Description:
Once in a lifetime parkside opportunity
Amazing family proportions, double zoning to Doncaster Secondary and Doncaster Gardens Primary and exclusive benefits opposite Ruffey Lake Park deliver an exceptional and tranquil lifestyle. Immaculately presented with the ambience of a north facing formal living and dining zone, enhanced by Jetmaster OFP, Colonial windows and high ceilings featuring throughout. Flowing through to superbly updated granite kitchen family/meals with s/s appliances including 5 gas jet burner and dishwasher. Connecting with a large casual living domain with elegant parquetry floors underfoot, integrating with undercover alfresco entertaining primed for all occasions with timber deck and OFP to enhance any BBQ. Overlooking a solar/gas-heated salt chlorinated swimming pool set in low maintenance landscaped gardens for hours of endless family fun.
Incredible accommodation comprises 5 bedrooms, BIRs, plus a study, 2 bathrooms and 2 powder rooms. The master presents a renovated ensuite with large shower and WIR and the upper bathroom provides for busy families with a double vanity, bath and separate WC. Complementing these proportions is a sizeable rumpus/games/theatre domain with garden views and an upper balcony with uninterrupted 180-degree park views. Vistas including Ruffey Lake Park, the athletics track, cricket pitch and the family pool can be appreciated every day from the comfort of your own home.
Resting in a pinnacle location just minutes to Westfield, Macedon Square, Jackson Court eateries and The Pines. Walk to Rieschiecks Reserve and sporting facilities. Close to Aquarena, walking tracks, city and Box Hill buses and the freeway.
Freshly painted throughout and further comfort afforded by GDH, evaporative cooling upstairs, split system, brand new quality carpets, security alarm, ducted vacuum, large laundry with laundry chute, Roman blinds and external north facing canvas blinds, ample storage throughout including utilities shed, watertanks 6000L combined and double remote garage with rear roller door entry suitable for a caravan/boat plus OSP.
Insights: 2 Waldau Court, Doncaster VIC 3108 was last sold in 2017 and 133 other 4 bedroom house in Doncaster have recently been sold.

Description:
Single-level style and convenience!
Generating instant appeal with its attractive façade and contemporary presentation, turn the key and step into a world of carefree living with this smart and stylish two-bedroom unit, located inside the highly-regarded Birralee Primary School and Koonung Secondary College catchment area.
Only a short stroll to Westfield Shoppingtown, Wilsons Rd Reserve, bus services and the Koonung Creek Trail and offering swift access to the Eastern Freeway, it’s the perfect find for those placing great importance on everyday convenience. And when you marry that with the fashionable single-level interior that’s easy to maintain, styled with modern timber floors and designed with two distinct living and entertaining zones, why would you choose to buy or invest anywhere else!
Indoor-outdoor living is a design feature embraced by the radiant living area, which extends onto the front terrace framed with easy-care landscaped gardens. It’s also a signature feature of the open-plan granite and stainless steel kitchen/meals area, which unites with the sensational entertainer’s deck that has summertime BBQs written all over it.
Both generous-sized bedrooms are serviced by a fantastic main bathroom, while indoor climate levels remain perfect all year long given the presence of evaporative cooling and ducted heating.
Completed with two toilets, remote garage and excellent proportions throughout, this practical and functional residence ticks all the boxes!

Description:
Peaceful, private, potential, perfect!
Supremely private, wonderfully proportioned and effortlessly convenient to a host of lifestyle assets that adorn this peaceful family-friendly neighbourhood, discover the charms of this pristine single-level family home and the potential it presents for the future.
Nestled amongst lovingly maintained gardens resplendent with fragrant roses, lilacs and numerous other blossoming plants, a sense of calm radiates throughout this tranquil property, which offers a view of the city skyline from the north-facing backyard hallmarked by its remarkable privacy, picture-perfect beauty and suitability for child's play.
A portico entry adds a secure element to this fantastic family home, which opens onto a beautiful and elegant formal lounge warmed by a gas log fireplace before arriving at a sizeable open-plan living area in the heart of the home. A well-appointed kitchen with quality appliances and walk-in pantry (with in-floor wine storage area) is perfectly proportioned for the home cook and allows you to keep an eye on the kids playing in the backyard, while French doors integrate the interior with the undercover entertaining area to create a desirable indoor-outdoor aspect.
Bedrooms are of a spacious nature (master with walk-in robe with hidden wine storage area and an elegant ensuite), while a separate study, fresh bathroom, separate laundry, evaporative cooling, ducted heating, polished timber flooring, high ceilings, remote double garage, separate workshop, solar panels and electric roller blinds in the kitchen and laundry adds further appeal to this outstanding family home.
Sited on a large 676sqm (approx.) allotment, there's also scope to follow the lead of others in the area and develop (STCA).
Located inside the Birralee Primary School and Koonung Secondary College catchment area, you'll also value the swift access to Westfield Shoppingtown, bus transport, Wilson Rd Reserve, the Eastern Freeway and the Park + Ride facility.

Description:
By George, it has the space you need in the location you crave!
You’ve heard the saying how they don’t build houses like they used to. Now you have the evidence to support it with this strong and solid, quality-built five-bedroom home.
Having been owned and lovingly maintained by only two owners in its lifetime, this secure gated residence has everything you want from a family home: the multiple living areas, zoned accommodation and modern conveniences. And in an added boost, the future occupants can also enjoy the prestige of living inside the coveted Doncaster Gardens Primary School and Doncaster Secondary College catchment area, within walking distance of Ruffey Lake Park, Tom Kelly Athletics Track and bus services and moments to Westfield Shoppingtown, Aquarena Leisure Centre and Jackson Court shops.
Enjoy views towards Ruffey Lake Park from the north-facing formal lounge and adjacent dining room, both of which exude an elegant character and expand onto the front balcony. Size and space, meanwhile, are desirable assets of the vast open-plan living area, which features a large timber kitchen (with quality appliances and pristine presentation) as its centrepiece.
All five bedrooms (master with walk-in robe and ensuite) enjoy the private sanctuary of the zoned accommodation wing, which also houses a large laundry and family bathroom.
A flat grassed backyard punctuated with an assortment of fruit trees is your very own fruit orchard, while disability lift access, ducted vacuum, ducted heating and cooling, video intercom, solar panels and a remote triple garage with access to a large concreted storage room and additional storage area under the house completes this appealing picture.

Eliminate any space issues you may have in an instant with this king-sized family home. Well designed for multi-generational living due to its living areas and spacious bedrooms indulge in luxury and space with this well-appointed residence.
Class and elegance defines the generously proportioned formal lounge and dining area, which is positioned near the open plan kitchen and captures the essence of contemporary living with its modern accents. All bedrooms feature built in robes, gas ducted heating and evaporative cooling throughout, making this home comfortable all year long.

Description:
Classic Australian beauty offers quiet family living
Showing off with an elevated block of 890 sqm (approx.), a considered floorplan which allows for spacious and graceful living zones, and magnificent quality that has stood the test of time, this generous 4 bedroom, 2 bathroom residence defines Doncaster living whisper quiet court.
With all the features of a classic Australian home, this single storey charmer is first time offered since its original build in 1982 by Ellison Rigby. Two formal zones towards the front of the dwelling are perfect for entertaining with family and friends, while a family room with a brick open fireplace has a vast amount of space for everyday living. The huge kitchen comes complete with a walk in pantry, quality appliances and overlooks the family room, with easy access outside to the wrap around garden.
The spacious master bedroom is located at the front of the house, and features a dressing room with built-in robes and an ensuite, while two of the other bedrooms come with BIRs and share a central bathroom with separate powder room. Other highlights include brand new carpets throughout, gas ducted heating, wide verandahs and double carport.
You'll have easy access to the CBD and further east thanks to the home's close proximity to the Eastern Freeway. Zoned for Doncaster Secondary College you are also near Kerrimuir Primary School, Koonung Creek Linear Park, Koonung Creek Trail, Jackson Court Shopping Centre, Westfield Doncaster Shopping Centre, Kerrimuir Shopping strip, and buses.

Description:
Big and spacious with a north-facing entertainer's backyard and a short walk to Westfield Shoppingtown!
Only a short stroll to Westfield Shoppingtown, bus transport, Ruffey Lake Park and St Gregory the Great Primary School, enrich your family's standard of living in more ways than you can imagine inside this light and bright, big and spacious and superbly crafted family home, nestled amongst beautifully landscaped gardens in a premier location within the Doncaster Primary School and Doncaster Secondary College catchment area.
Boasting a breathtaking north-facing backyard, which entertains as well as it calms the mind, on a coveted 742sqm (approx.) allotment with DDO8 zoning, there's also scope to develop up to three modern townhouses (STCA). But just because you can develop (STCA), it doesn't mean you have to, particularly considering the pristine condition of this lovingly maintained residence.
With two separate living zones, your young, growing family will never get in each other's way - only when it's time for dinner! An incredible sense of size and space extends to the spacious bedrooms, all of which are zoned on a private accommodation wing, which also houses a separate study, fully-tiled family bathroom and two-way ensuite that connects with the Master bedroom.
The peaceful and private nature of the elegant L-shaped formal lounge/dining is sure to please, as will the seamless integration between the stunning family living and undercover entertainer's deck, which looks across the north-facing backyard meticulously landscaped with picture-perfect gardens and a paved entertaining area.
A central kitchen is well equipped and proportioned to cater for a growing family, while the presence of ducted heating, split-system heating/cooling, alarm, garden shed, 3,000-litre water tank, generous off-street parking and easy access to the Eastern Freeway adds further appeal.

Description:
FANTASTIC FIRST HOME
This delightful solidly built and well maintained 2 bedroom unit has to appeal to those seeking their first home. It's light bright and spacious and set amidst a unique and attractive village style complex.
With a large carpeted lounge room adjoining the spacious kitchen and meals area together with a family bathroom and two good sized bedrooms it would ideally suit a small family as it comprises an undercover outdoor entertaining area adjoining a large and attractive rear yard.
Location wise it is a beauty, with a gate accessing the popular walking track leading to Ruffey Lake Park just 550 metres away, while Aquarena too is within strolling distance. Public transport is at your doorstep and Templestowe Village, Macedon Square and Mega shopping complex Westfield are all just moments away too!
Comprising a single lock up garage with parking for an additional vehicle and set in a delightful garden setting, this great little unit represents a fantastic buy!

Description:
A Property of Position and Potential
Enjoying a peaceful position in the middle of a safe and secure complex, this spacious and perfectly positioned apartment lends itself to a range of options.
Whether you're looking to make that all important first step onto the property ladder or for a solid investment with plenty of scope for improvement, this is one that ticks a lot of boxes.
An open lounge, kitchen and dining area welcomes you in where plenty of natural light is enjoyed from west facing windows which connect seamlessly to a fantastic private outdoor balcony.
With electric upright cooking and oven, ample storage and bench space, a tiled splash back and additional shelving, the kitchen really forms the central hub of the home.
A spacious master bedroom has multiple built-in robes and access to the bright bathroom which incorporates a corner shower, vanity and toilet.
The addition of a single lock up garage, access to the complex's laundry facilities and with a bus stop right out the front, a more comfortable and convenient apartment would be hard to find.
Located walking distance to the magnificent Westfield Shoppingtown, close to Doncaster primary and secondary schooling and with great connection to Doncaster Road, Eastland and the city via Eastlink, this exciting offering is sure to go to the top of your list.
